g.text: Acele: "What do you want to know?" She smiles a little.
You: "What is this pilgrimage you're talking about?"
"Sure. You helped us out, I can repay the favour. What do you want to know?"
Acele: "Andre? He's a cool guy. Doesn't really come off as one, but he is. To me at least..."
Acele: "Actually, we don't know where he's from. Or who he is, really."
You: "What does he think he's doing when he yells all that stuff?"
You: "Where's he from? How long has he been with you guys?"
You: "But I'm a police officer. You *have* to answer me."
Acele: "Sir," she gives you a switchblade smile. "I abide by *the law*."
Acele: "What do you want to know?"
"I told you, I'm a silver bird."
Acele: "Egg came with us. He made this wheezing puppy dog sound all the way back. Couldn't even speak."
Jump to: [Acele: ""Who do you want to know about?""]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Unfortunately, I can confirm that."
Jump to: [tellin about dudes hub EGG]
Acele: "One time we were out partying, somewhere in backwater Faubourg. Or maybe even Coal City, I can't remember. Maybe it was Coal City..."
You: "Oh, and I'm also a raging fascist who doesn't approve of *different people* -- so no, I don't think I'll be going."
Acele: "He abides by the hard core, sir. You would have to ask him yourself."
You: "What kind of mindset is that?"
You: "There's more to you than you let on. What am I not seeing?"
Acele: "It means I don't answer questions about myself."
You: "You don't have to tell *me* rock music is dead. I abandoned rock music a long time ago. Can't disco to rock!"
"You don't have to tell *me* rock is backward. I am The Futureman. I abandoned rock in the Thirties. Stupid rock." (Spit.)
Jump to: [Acele: ""Who do you want to know about?""]
Acele: "I've never seen him so psyched about anything though -- and he's often psyched. Looked sort of desperate, like it's his last chance or something. Or maybe he was just high..."
Jump to: [Acele: ""Who do you want to know about?""]
Acele: "Okay, then you should go and take a look, I guess. Boogie Street is cool. It's got a lot of immigrants and all kinds of different people."
You: "Relax, girl. I am a police officer, but I'm perfectly corrupt. You can tell me about drugs and shit, I don't care."
"Relax girl. We're police officers, but we're corrupt, rotten to the marrow. You can tell us about drugs and shit, I don't give fuck."
You: "I might just do that if I make it there alive."
You: "We certainly saw that in practice, didn't we?"
Jump to: [tellin about dudes hub EGG]
Inland Empire: A strange feeling... Every now and then, something feels off about the way she speaks. She doesn't change tone, but you feel as though there's more about her than she lets on.
You: "What does he do up there?"

Acele: "Anodic music doesn't really do vocals in the traditional sense. Vocals are thought of as *rock*. That's to say they're a bit *backward*. No offence if you like rock music, though. Rock music is cool by me."
You: "Yes, I forgot. Tell me about yourself."
Acele: "I mean, not that he does drugs. Just *high* you know."
Acele: "He's a carpenter. Trained and all. He's very good, he just doesn't have the mindset to work like that -- in a shop somewhere."
Acele: "Yeah," she says, then opens her mouth like she's about to add something, but doesn't.
"Yeah," she says, then adds: "I hope you do."
You: "Oh, I'm sorry... have I not told you I'm a raging alcoholic who recently drank himself into an oblivion so deep he can't even remember what sounds like the biggest street in the city?"
You: "Oh, he talks to Noid? What for?"

Acele: "It was definitely Coal City, because it took us two days to walk back to the Fau. He just wheezed the whole way, we never really asked him why he came with us. Or who he was. I think his name is Germaine..."
Acele: "They do say death is an avenue. Like all the others." She's silent for a second like she's going to add something. But she doesn't.
"They do say death is an avenue like any other." She's silent for a second. "I still think you'll make it to Boogie Street, though."
"They do say death is an avenue like any other." She's silent for a second. "I still think you'll make it to Boogie Street, though."
You: "No, I meant for breakfast. Of course for a living."
You: "Is that because of his beliefs? The hard core and the ribs, the... spinal cord and stuff?"
"That's because Noid is violently hard core. I have internalized it. I understand why he doesn't stoop to servitude. Do you?"
Jump to: [Acele: ""What do you want to know?""]
Reaction Speed: There's that phrase again. It really reminds you of... *something*.
Jump to: [tellin about dudes hub EGG]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Anyway..." He looks around, a little embarrassed of the enthusiasm of his interjection.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I understand. People are usually afraid to do things if others aren't already doing them. Dancing makes you dance like sneezing makes you sneeze. Or yawning makes you..."
Acele: "Anyway, even if you don't have vocals you still need someone to say something every now and then, right? To urge things on. That's where the party boy comes in..."
Conceptualization: Ptew ptew! Sweeesh! Your credentials as the resident Futureman of Revachol are being questioned. Show her you're hip with the times, gramps!
Acele: "He basically just stands on the stage and dances and yells how awesome everything is. It's very catchy."
Acele: "Sure..." she says, slightly disoriented. "What do you want to know?"
Acele: "He's real hard core about the lifestyle."
Jump to: [Acele: ""Who do you want to know about?""]
Acele: "Beats me... Noid said they get along, somehow. They're both crazy enough, I guess."
Acele: "Come to think of it, yes!" She laughs.
You: "Could it be that he's balding? Him thinking it's his last chance?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "That would depend on the circumstances." The lieutenant taps his foot.
Acele: "Alright." She picks up the tape recorder and looks you in the eye...
Acele: "I just try to stay away from the crab-man, but he talks to Noid. They seem to have some 'thing' going on."

Encyclopedia: The worst of the *banlieues*. A wretched heap of closed-down mines even west of Jamrock, on the dusty slope of Mont Martin. The remotest possible area of Revachol, no one even wants to exploit those people anymore.
Acele: "Oh, the crab-man." She shudders. "Still gives me the creeps, the way he moves... But he doesn't actually come down that much, just climbs around the rafters."
You: "Okay, lets leave it at that then."
Empathy: You can see it must have been a great night. The memory causes her to go silent for a moment or two.
Acele: "It's just something poor Faubourg kids do every spring, to pass the time. We walk the entire length of Boogie Street, up to Jamrock. Or as much as possible."
You: "What's the deal with Egg Head?"
Acele: "Nothing. But then again... there's nothing to organize around here either. He really wants this church thing to work..."
You: "What do you think of the crab-man?"
Acele: "Is there a law that would stop me from lying, though?"

Acele: "Egg was yelling along to some jams someone was spinning, all night long. Just kept yelling until he didn't have a shred of voice left. When the sun came up over the mines... there were mines? Yeah, it was in Coal City!" She nods.
You: "It's unlikely I'll make it there. Chest pains. Need to continue drinking. But thank you."
Empathy: A quick response. She's very sure of it. He's someone she feels she can trust and even control, if need be.
You: "Acele who? I'm not a young suitor, this is official police business."
Acele: "I don't know man, have you *been* down Boogie Street? It's a little bewildering."
Acele: "Who do you want to know about?"

Inland Empire: A strange feeling... like before, when you caught her lying better than she should have. Every now and then something feels off about the way she speaks. She doesn't exactly change tone, but you feel as though there's more about her than she lets on.
Perception (Sight): She rubs her sides, but not from cold. Her shoulders are relaxed. She must have taken a hit or she's on an upswing.
Acele: "He's a Faubourger I guess, like the rest of us. Okay, maybe not Egg, I don't know about him, but Noid and the rest are from Faubourg, making the pilgrimage up north to visit The Paliseum."
Inland Empire: This is the first time you've heard her laugh.
Inland Empire: You wish you'd been there.
You: "Let's say I *haven't* been down Boogie Street."
Acele: "People are sweet," she says quietly.
You: "I'm from the police. It's for the paperwork."
"Did I not say I was from the police? It's for the paperwork."
"Uhm... kind of? I'm gonna say: yes."
Jump to: [tellin about dudes hub EGG]
Perception (Sight): Her hair is dyed blonde, with dark roots showing. There's a coarseness to her features, some masculinity below that timidness.
"He told me as much, but what exactly is a party boy?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, I suppose we did."
You: "God damn right, rock music is the coolest. Rock music forever!"
Acele: "He takes care of shit. Sorry, I mean he's got a *vision*. Of what life should be, you know? He tries to push things until everything falls into place. He's an organizer."
Acele: "What do you mean, 'do'? Like for a living?"
Acele: "Wow. You really *have* talked to him." She smiles. "Indeed. Noid serves no master but the beat."
Acele: "Who knows?" She shrugs. "He doesn't really answer our questions, see. Not that it's easy to ask them. What are we supposed to do, yell up at the tower?"
You: "Actually, tell me about the others."
Acele: "Must have taken it as a sign when he found it abandoned like that. Said it was an *augury*. I don't know where he got that from." She smiles. "Andre's not super intelligent..."
Reaction Speed: Hang on, that phrase. You're suddenly reminded of... *something*.
Acele: "Uh... she's a bit odd, I have to say. Doesn't talk much. I'm not really sure how to vibe with her, y'know? Seems like she's not in a very good mood most of the time."
Acele: "He's in some kind of a self-destruction mode with that hair of his. Bleaching it like that. Probably wants to get rid of it altogether."

Acele: "But earlier today she told me about... welkins?" Acele grimaces, as if it's the first time hearing the word. "And she seemed oddly happy. Like she had had some idea with those... little creatures. Some artistic idea. I didn't really listen, I was busy with my mic."
Jump to: [Acele: ""Who do you want to know about?""]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yeah. Drugs. Shit. Fuck. We don't care." He smirks.
You: "Because I'm not. Now tell me something else about Noid."
Acele: "Okay." She shrugs. "To each his own."
Acele: "Oh, that... he's the party boy."
Acele: "Not to sound too dramatic, but I wouldn't make light of his belief system when he's around. Noid's a serious person. He's serious about the lifestyle."
Authority: You have little reason to doubt that's her real name, but... she's not all that surprised by this cop-show questioning, is she?
